Fire destroyed hundreds of houses at Kangemi Beach slums on Thursday evening. Residents said the fire may have been caused by a gas cylinder explosion in one of the houses. One person was injured while other residents lost property. Lucy Njeri, a resident, said she was at work when she received a phone call from her 12-year-old daughter to go back home because of the fire incident. "My daughter called me to came home at around 5:30pm. We could not save anything because the fire had already spread," she said. Residents said the response by firefighters, adding they went to the scene an hour after being alerted.